# id: MessageHandler -> void handleMessage(Message<?> message) throws MessagingException_
commentText:
Handles the message if possible. If the handler cannot deal with the_message this will result in a {@code MessageRejectedException} e.g._in case of a Selective Consumer. When a consumer tries to handle a_message, but fails to do so, a {@code MessageHandlingException} is_thrown. In the last case it is recommended to treat the message as tainted_and go into an error scenario._

_When the handling results in a failure of another message being sent_(e.g. a "reply" message), that failure will trigger a_{@code MessageDeliveryException}.__@param message the message to be handled_reply related to the handling of the message
